While recent changes in climate are shaping species-level differences in phenology, for many species their temporal niches may also reflect their evolutionary history. Species traits in communities today are the result of selective pressures acting over evolutionary timescales that include the historical climates and related ancestral phenotypes that were favourable under those previous conditions \citep{Wiens2010}. This could produce greater similarity in phenological traits of more closely related species \citep{Davies2013, Morales2024}, which would impact how species will respond to future climates.  \\ %emwSep26 -- I think you have a few too many of sentences like the one at the end here so I cut it and edited the point to be less repetitive. 
